---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — NTE Codex"
  description="How NTE Codex handles cookies, analytics, advertising and reader comments."
>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Last updated: 2026-05-11</p>

  <div class="prose-game max-w-prose">
    <p>
      NTE Codex is operated by an independent creator. This page explains what
      data the site collects, why, and how to ask for its removal.
    </p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Analytics:</strong> Google Analytics 4 records page visits,
        referrer, device type, and approximate geolocation (city / region).
        Data is aggregated; we don't identify individual readers.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Advertising:</strong> This site uses Google AdSense to
        display ads. AdSense uses cookies to serve ads based on your prior
        visits to this and other websites. Google's use of advertising
        cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads to you based on
        your visits to this site and/or other sites on the Internet. You
        can opt out of personalised advertising by visiting Google's
        <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Ads Settings</a>,
        or opt out of third-party vendor use of cookies for personalised
        ads via
        <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">aboutads.info</a>.
        Consent for personalised vs non-personalised ads is collected via
        the Google-certified Consent Management Platform (CMP) banner shown
        on your first visit; you can change your choice any time by
        clearing cookies for this domain.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Reader comments &amp; contact form:</strong> if you submit a
        comment or contact message we store:
        <ul>
          <li><em>Name</em> — optional; an empty name renders as "Anonymous".</li>
          <li><em>Message content</em> — required, up to 2000 characters.</li>
          <li><em>IP address</em> — kept for 30 days as an anti-abuse signal.</li>
          <li><em>User agent</em> — same purpose; 30 days.</li>
          <li>
            <em>Cloudflare Turnstile token</em> — used once to confirm you're
            not a bot, then discarded.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <strong>All comments are reviewed before publishing.</strong> Approved
        comments stay public until you ask for removal (see below).
      </li>
      <li><strong>No accounts.</strong> The site has no login system.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      On your first visit a Google-certified Consent Management Platform
      (CMP) banner asks whether you Consent / Manage Options / Decline.
      Once you choose, AdSense and Google Analytics 4 set their cookies
      accordingly. You can revisit your choice by clearing site data for
      <code>ntecodex.com</code> in your browser settings.
    </p>

    <h2>Removing your data</h2>
    <p>
      To delete a comment you wrote, submit a new comment on the same article
      with the subject line "Delete request" and enough detail to identify
      the original (rough timestamp + a phrase from the text is fine). We
      process delete requests within 7 days.
    </p>
    <p>
      For analytics opt-out: EU/UK users can use
      <a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">YourOnlineChoices</a>;
      US users can use
      <a href="https://optout.aboutads.info/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">AdChoices</a>.
      Or use a browser-level "Do Not Track" / tracker-blocking extension.
    </p>

    <h2>Data retention</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>IP addresses + user agents on messages: <strong>30 days</strong>.</li>
      <li>Approved comment text + name: indefinitely (until delete request).</li>
      <li>Rejected / spam-flagged messages: 90 days, then purged.</li>
      <li>Analytics: standard GA4 retention (default 2 months on this site).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Third-party services</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Google Analytics — see
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Google's privacy policy</a>.
      </li>
      <li>
        Google AdSense — see
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Google ads policy</a>.
      </li>
      <li>
        Cloudflare — site hosting, DDoS mitigation, and Turnstile bot
        verification. See
        <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Cloudflare privacy</a>.
      </li>
      <li>
        Supabase — backend storage for the comment moderation queue. See
        <a href="https://supabase.com/privacy" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Supabase privacy</a>.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      The "Last updated" date at the top reflects the current revision. We do
      not email readers about policy changes (we have no mailing list); please
      re-read this page if you've left a comment recently.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
